and

For maximum or minimum value of \(f(x)\), \(f'(x)=0\)

\[\Rightarrow \cos x=-\cos 2x\]

\({\mkern1mu\raise1pt\hbox{.}\mkern1mu\raise4pt\hbox{.}\mkern1mu\raise1pt\hbox{.}\mkern1mu} x=\pi \pm 2x\) or \(x=\cfrac{\pi }{3} ,\, \, -\pi \)

Now ;

\(f''\, \left(\cfrac{\pi }{3} \right)=-2\sin \cfrac{2\pi }{3} -\sin \cfrac{\pi }{3} =-2\cfrac{\sqrt{3} }{2} -\cfrac{\sqrt{3} }{2} =-\cfrac{3\sqrt{3} }{2} =-ve\)

Hence \(f(x)\)is maximum at \(x=\cfrac{\pi }{3} \).
